On July 18, 2020, a proclamation was issued to honor the memory and public service of Representative John Lewis of Georgia. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, all public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in Washington, D.C., and throughout the United States and its territories and possessions until July 18, 2020. The flag will also be flown at half-staff during the same period at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The proclamation was signed on July 18, 2020.